---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Reveal from "@/components/atoms/Reveal.astro";
import LabCard from "@/components/molecules/LabCard.astro";
import { getShowcaseLabProjects } from "@/data/lab";

const projects = getShowcaseLabProjects();
const stats = [
  { value: String(projects.length).padStart(2, "0"), label: "Projects, deliberately shortlisted" },
  { value: "Inspect → test", label: "The recurring obsession" },
  { value: "Figma ↔ code", label: "Where the experiments live" },
];
---
<BaseLayout title="Lab" description="Five evidence-backed experiments in AI evaluation, agent behavior, conversation design, and design tooling.">
  <div class="page container">
    <Reveal>
      <h1 class="page-header__title">Lab</h1>
    </Reveal>

    <div class="spacer-md"></div>

    <Reveal class="lab-intro">
      <p>Generation got cheap before evaluation got good. So most of my experiments circle the less glamorous questions: how do you specify behaviour, inspect what changed, review a user flow, and leave enough evidence for another person to disagree?</p>
      <p>These are the five I would actually put in front of a hiring manager. Some work end to end; some are precise prototypes for tools I wish existed. Most were pair-programmed with Claude. I supplied the problem, the product judgement, and a suspicious number of tiny corrections.</p>
    </Reveal>

    <Reveal>
      <div class="lab-stat-row">
        {stats.map((s) => (
          <div>
            <p class="lab-stat__value">{s.value}</p>
            <p class="lab-stat__label">{s.label}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </Reveal>

    <section class="lab-category">
      <Reveal class="lab-category__head">
        <h2 class="section-label">Five worth a proper look</h2>
        <span class="lab-category__count">{String(projects.length).padStart(2, "0")}</span>
      </Reveal>
      <div class="lab-grid">
        {projects.map((project, i) => (
          <Reveal delay={i * 60}>
            <LabCard project={project} />
          </Reveal>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <Reveal class="lab-archive-note">
      <p>There are smaller utilities, marketing sites, and half-finished experiments too. I left them off this page because a portfolio should be a point of view, not a downloads folder.</p>
    </Reveal>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
